SIMPLE: galactin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galactin
<hw>Ga*lac"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
milk. Cf. <er>Lactin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>An amorphous, gelatinous substance containing nitrogen, found in
milk and other animal fluids. It resembles peptone, and is variously
regarded as a coagulating or emulsifying agent.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A white waxy substance found in the sap of the South American cow
tree (<gen>Galactodendron</gen>).</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>An amorphous,
gummy carbohydrate resembling gelose, found in the seeds of leguminous
plants, and yielding on decomposition several sugars, including
galactose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

